  (text "ideal diodes are an idea, LM74700\nbut they use 100 uA which is too much for amorphous panels\nmax40203 might work\n\ndiodes are doubled to provide the nets without sequential voltage loss"
    (at 177.8 24.13 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid 0abf763f-9ebf-4e73-ad4c-b22a956db844)
  )
  (text "Every part must be considered for leakage current" (at 12.7 196.85 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid 0f7c4b2a-6784-4aa9-86ad-8c6c47c1d3b9)
  )
  (text "EN can take a PWM signal, but no room here\nN-channel FET\nDrain = EN\nSource = attiny pin\nGate = VLEDCAP\nGate series 1M resistor and 47 nF cap\n\nFET and RC to prevent\nlatch low conditions\n\nVLEDCAP off voltage out, needs diode and large capacitor (47 uF) to\npower MCU during voltage outages PWM pulses of the regulator"
    (at 149.86 55.88 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid 1df9415b-aa8e-4dc7-947b-be8a3b2baae8)
  )
  (text "Red (1.5V - 2.2V) + ELDC + max 2.76 solar\nGreen (2.5 - 3.2V) + Hybrid + 3.4/4.2V solar\nWhite (2.2 - 2.7) + large ELDC +  larger max 2.76 solar"
    (at 13.97 190.5 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid 27614a4d-e316-4cab-a726-71fdd49e8fe2)
  )
  (text "Light only on in dark" (at 128.27 156.21 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid 35e7518b-145c-4af2-9170-be2d436eb5e5)
  )
  (text "The OSRAM PointLED defaults to giant pads\nThose are just for heat dissipation, can be smaller"
    (at 83.82 29.21 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid 4c58e57f-6739-4f12-b9cc-cf6471738883)
  )
  (text "Rref = 120 / target mA" (at 58.42 39.37 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid 56ea09ae-5258-47ba-ae90-919713323eee)
  )
  (text "After top layer PCB assembly\n1. Solder LEDs\n2. Program and test MCU (with EN switch off)\n3. Apply conformal coating (not through holes), to earring basket, solar panel edge\n4. Solder solar panel\n5. Solder earring in with silver solder\n6. Apply conformal coating to earring on backside\n7. Solder capacitors"
    (at 162.56 97.79 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid 7776cdc7-d60d-406d-8edd-e69c76c1d844)
  )
  (text "Minor danger here: make sure at least one LED\nis always on\n\nno room for fet gate resistors\nthis should be fine,\nwith low frequency and low gate capacitance"
    (at 45.72 87.63 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid 8079782a-edc3-412b-b07f-e8aa9e1ae8d4)
  )
  (text "One warm, one cool white\n0R replaced with LED for series (higher voltage) if red used"
    (at 83.82 38.1 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid 84539b8a-1de9-4c88-89ae-fa1925b814f1)
  )
  (text "240 µs wakeup time" (at 44.45 15.24 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid 8f014df6-2680-4b13-9ff1-7f13702d7df3)
  )
  (text "Brownout\nturbo only when voltage > 2.4V\nbrownout detection whenever run, set to ~1.8V\nturn on next led first, then off the current led\n\nimmediately set FET3 ON, then continue"
    (at 173.99 144.78 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid 9a417c03-ad6c-4d65-aee4-74b749c44518)
  )
  (text "Light sensor\ninput on solar panel\ninput on supercap\nIMU\nbutton"
    (at 149.86 119.38 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid 9dd0aed7-5426-45bb-8329-f35812c15995)
  )
  (text "pin with shunt jumper\nas tiny \"switch\"" (at 20.32 58.42 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid adcea26b-cb42-4524-b8ff-f9991517785b)
  )
  (text "Stone (as earring) connections" (at 15.24 127 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid bfdd3c12-d739-448b-bbe1-427f97a26d02)
  )
  (text "ESD energy collector, for fun\nbecause there is space at this end of board"
    (at 49.53 106.68 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid c78ed647-b9ed-4be7-aeff-d614cf0d236b)
  )

